    "victoryCondition": {
        "condition": "Cathrin has obtained a full D.R.A.K.K.E.N. license through any means — whether by striking a deal with Everett Crain, having DavKit crack the system, or finding another path entirely — and has survived the 90-day deadline with the system fully activated and her life no longer in immediate danger.",
        "text": "The countdown is over. The license key accepted. D.R.A.K.K.E.N. hums in your chest — not the anxious stutter of trial mode, but a deep, steady resonance. For the first time in ninety days, you take a breath without wondering if it will be your last.\n\nYou are no longer Cathrin Kardashev, data-entry clerk from New York, tourist, victim. You are something new — something with scales and fire and a future you carved out of a world that tried to throw you away.\n\nWhatever comes next, you'll face it with your own heart beating in your chest. Even if that heart is made of chrome.",
