            "id": "RGjEdNzQl",
            "name": "DRAKKEN",
            "content": "D.R.A.K.K.E.N. stands for Draconic Reconstructive Adaptive Kinetic-Kill Enhancement Network. It is a classified military chrome system developed by Agro Dynamic Incorporated. When implanted, it begins as a heart-sized mass of chrome and biocompatible wiring. Over time it integrates with the host's biology, slowly transforming them into a combat-capable dragon-like humanoid — growing claws, reinforced teeth, a tail, and dragon-inspired tactical systems. The system can replace damaged organs and even entire limbs with chrome equivalents if the originals are destroyed. DRAKKEN includes an onboard AI sharing its name that provides tactical support and battlefield awareness to the host. The system requires a valid license code within 90 days of activation or it shuts down completely — including any organs it has replaced. This is standard anti-piracy DRM, not a deliberate kill switch, which makes it worse. The player character Cathrin Polk was never meant to receive DRAKKEN. It was implanted accidentally when its transport crashed into her, and the system activated autonomously to repair her fatal injuries.",
