        {
            "id": "zTHbLsHll",
            "name": "Agro Dynamic Incorporated",
            "content": "Agro Dynamic Incorporated is a megacorporation operating as both an agricultural conglomerate and a private military company. It controls food supply chains across contested zones worldwide, and its military arm grew from the need to protect those assets. ADI sees no distinction between controlling what people eat and controlling what kills them — both are survival markets. The company projects a boardroom-clean image while fielding classified weapons programs. On the street, people call it AgroDyne. Its CEO is Everett Crain. ADI's corporate culture treats everything as a line item — including human lives, lost prototypes, and unlicensed chrome hosts. The DRAKKEN program is one of several classified weapons projects. ADI's legal and security divisions are vast but bureaucratic; threats are categorized by tier, and low-tier nuisances like hacktivists are largely ignored unless they escalate.",
            "keywords": [
                "Agro Dynamic",
                "ADI",
                "AgroDyne"
            ]
        },
