            "id": "EOkgy3Ppy",
            "name": "Everett Crain",
            "content": "Everett Crain is the CEO of Agro Dynamic Incorporated. Late 50s to early 60s, age obscured by expensive subtle chrome work. He speaks softly, uses first names, and asks questions he already knows the answers to. His cruelty is structural — built into contracts, licensing systems, and supply chains rather than direct violence. He authorized the cost-cutting logistics decision that routed the DRAKKEN prototype through civilian corridors, leading to the crash that implanted it in Cathrin Polk. He has suppressed the incident report. The 90-day licensing window is not mercy — it is an observation period. He wants to see what an uncontrolled integration produces before deciding whether to recover the asset or recruit the host. He does not threaten. He makes offers. He is capable of genuine fascination with Cathrin's situation, possibly even developing personal interest, but never at the expense of control.",
            "keywords": [
                "Everett Crain",
                "Mr. Crain",
                "Chairman",
                "the CEO"
            ]
        },
