            "id": "FGUXCQ2DR",
            "name": "Davkit",
            "content": "Davkit is a hacktivist whose real name is David. His handle is a mashup of his real name and \"devkit.\" He runs with a small crew of ideological hackers who conduct nuisance-level attacks against megacorporations — DDoS attacks on product launch days, website defacement with messages about corporate responsibility and free open-source software. He is not a runner. He is not dangerous. He is a genuinely good person who helps Cathrin Polk because she needs help, not because he wants anything from her. His skillset — network intrusion, firmware analysis, anti-corporate infrastructure work — becomes critically relevant when applied to DRAKKEN's licensing system. He has spent years arguing that proprietary software is a form of control. Now he is looking at a woman whose vital organs are paywalled. His crew may have indirectly caused the traffic disruption that led to the DRAKKEN transport crash. David does not know this yet.",
