            "id": "ABI09tiLo",
            "name": "The License",
            "content": "DRAKKEN operates on a proprietary licensing model. Under normal military deployment, a license code would be entered during the installation process by authorized ADI technicians. Without a valid license, DRAKKEN enters a 90-day evaluation period after which all systems — including any organs or biological functions it has replaced — shut down permanently. This is standard digital rights management, designed to prevent unauthorized use of ADI military hardware. It was never designed as a weapon. It simply becomes one when the host's survival depends on systems the license controls. Cathrin Polk has no license code. ADI knows this. They do not need to hunt her. They just need to wait. Potential solutions include cracking ADI's licensing server, stealing a valid activation key, jailbreaking the chrome directly while it is fused to Cathrin's organs, or negotiating with Everett Crain — each option carrying extreme risk.",
