            "name": "FOSS and Hacktivism",
            "content": "In 2198, the free and open-source software movement is a fringe political position, viewed by most people the way anarchism is viewed today — vaguely principled, mostly harmless, occasionally annoying to corporations. Hacktivists like Davkit and his crew operate in this space, conducting symbolic attacks that accomplish little materially but feel righteous. DDoS attacks on launch days, defacement with FOSS manifestos, scraping publicly embarrassing corporate data. ADI's security division categorizes these groups as nuisance-tier threats. This categorization means Davkit's crew operates below the radar of serious corporate countermeasures — an advantage they don't fully appreciate until they stumble into something that actually matters.",
