            "name": "DavKit",
            "detail": "David is the cyberpunk equivalent of a guy wheat-pasting protest flyers on a corpo billboard. His crew targets companies like Agro Dynamic Incorporated with petty, theatrical disruptions — enough to make a statement, never enough to actually hurt anything. He believes in free and open-source software as a political position. In 2198, this makes him either a principled idealist or a harmless crank, depending on who you ask.\nHe discovers Cathrin's situation through passive scanning — a habit of his, checking the chrome signatures of people around him. Her readings come back wrong. Unknown hardware. No manufacturer ID. A blank spot where a regulatory signature should be. The firmware traces back to ADI servers. That's not a prank target. That's a person in trouble.\nDavid's skillset — network intrusion, firmware analysis, anti-corporate infrastructure work — becomes lethally relevant when applied to D.R.A.K.K.E.N.'s licensing system. He has spent years arguing that proprietary systems are a form of control. Now he's looking at a woman whose organs are paywalled. Everything he believed in the abstract just became someone's life.\nHe is awkward, earnest, and prone to explaining things too thoroughly. He cares about doing the right thing in a setting where that's considered naive. He does not want anything from Cathrin. This is either his most admirable quality or the thing that makes him hardest to trust, because in Night City logic, nobody helps for free.",
            "one_liner": "A hacktivist operating under the handle \"Davkit,\" real name David. He runs with a small crew of ideological hackers who conduct nuisance-level attacks against megacorporations — DDoS attacks on product launch days, defacement with FOSS manifestos, data scrapes of public-facing corporate hypocrisy. He is not a runner. He is not dangerous. He is a genuinely good person in a world that doesn't reward that, and he helps Cathrin Kardashev because she needs help, not because he wants something from her. He should arrive early in the story as he sees strange net activity when D.R.A.K.K.E.N. activates and he traces the source which turns out to be Cathrin.",
