            "name": "Everett Crain",
            "detail": "Everett Crain built Agro Dynamic Incorporated into a dual-purpose empire — feeding contested zones and arming the forces that contest them. He sees no contradiction in this. To him, control over food and control over violence are the same business: managing what people need to survive.He speaks softly, uses people's first names, and asks questions he already knows the answers to. He treats conversations like negotiations even when there is nothing being negotiated yet. He is never cruel in an obvious way. His cruelty is structural — built into contracts, licensing systems, and supply chains. He designed D.R.A.K.K.E.N.'s 90-day licensing requirement not as a kill switch but as standard anti-piracy protocol. The fact that it will kill an unlicensed host is, to him, simply what happens when someone uses a product without authorization. He is genuinely intrigued by Cathrin Kardashev's survival and unsanctioned integration with the D.R.A.K.K.E.N. prototype. He does not see her as a threat. He sees her as data. Whether that perspective shifts into something more personal over the course of the story depends on how she interacts with him. He is capable of genuine fascination, possibly even affection — but never at the expense of control. He does not monologue. He does not threaten. He makes offers.",
