    "designNotes": "--- Original user world design prompt: ---\n\nIn the cyberpunk dystopia of 2198 Cathrin Kardashev a member of the small middle class that still gets to go on vacations every few years was in Akihabara visiting Japan from New York for an anime convention when suddenly her world goes black only to wake in an ally later with military chrome she could never dream of purchasing. She was identified as a tourist and grabbed by black market organ harvesters. They took everything they could sell and threw her body in a dumpster, but the harvesters also threw a bit of chrome that kept asking for a license code in the bin with her because they couldn't get it to work. That bit of chrome was D.R.A.K.K.E.N. or Draconic Reconstructive Adaptive Kinetic-Kill Enhancement Network it starts as a heart size chunk of chrome and wire but when implanted into a person slowly turns them in a combat capable dragon like human complete with tail claws teeth and dragon inspired gadgets. The chrome can replace organs even whole limbs if destroyed in battle and come with an AI with the same name as the system that provides tactical support. D.R.A.K.K.E.N. was developed by Agro Dynamic Incorporated, or as it's known on the street AgroDyne, originally just a agricultural company as resources became strained the world over they profits grew and the source of those profits needed protection thus they spun up a private military contract division that provided the soldiers and R&D needed for the project. D.R.A.K.K.E.N. was intercepted by the harvesters when an Agro Dynamic Incorporated runner was harvested. Now with D.R.A.K.K.E.N. in Cathrin's empty chest cavity it did what it was built to do and turned her into a living weapon. The player will play as Cathrin as she needs to navigate her new body and all the complications having a secret military project for a heart comes with. The story will start with her waking up in the ally 'naked' she's not wearing clothes but most of her body has been replaced with dragon like chrome. Her body still humanoid, but now with cyber dragon tail, claws, scales, and teeth in a human shaped jaw. D.R.A.K.K.E.N. asking for a license key that Cathrin has no way of knowing limiting her to D.R.A.K.K.E.N. trail mode which will limit her daily usage of the powers the system can grant her and frequently reminding her to visit a Agro Dynamic Incorporated customer care facility to sort out the license issue. D.R.A.K.K.E.N. isn't sentient, but can adapt and is programmed with dragon themed motivational quotes it will occasionally blurt out if the user is in low mood. Whether Cathrin seeks out an Agro Dynamic Incorporated customer care facility or not she will attract the personal attention of the Agro Dynamic Incorporated CEO Everett Crain who is more than willing to sell back Cathrin's lost organs, not her's specifically but still organs, in exchange for her service. Service holds many meaning in this context Everett Crain is the dark romance shadow daddy and he is interested in owing Cathrin so service can mean many things. Whether the player begrudgingly or excitedly submits to Everett Crain should be at the player discretion. Everett Crain isn't the only option David or as most of the world knows him DavKit is a small time hackivist, the kind that launches anonymous ddos attacks on launch day with a message about corporate responsibility and FOSS. DavKit is in a coffee shop near the ally scanning for vulnerable ports when D.R.A.K.K.E.N. comes online. D.R.A.K.K.E.N. being a PMC secret isn't broadcasting normal IDs immediately making DavKit suspicious. In a dark cyberpunk world someone idealistic trying to help you for free can be scarier then the devils you know like a CEO trying to own you which is why DavKit isn't the obvious romantic choice, he's genuinely just a good guy trying to do his best without hurting anyone. Cathrin needs the license before the 90 day free trail period runs out or the D.R.A.K.K.E.N. acting as all of her major organs will stop functioning. That leaves her with few choices, Davkit's genuine desire to help people or the devil she knows in Everett Crain. If she chooses Everett Crain she'll become a sexy attack dog serving the company and servicing Everett Crain until he's board of her. If she choose Davkit there's a chance for a genuine loving romance or none at all as Davkit is willing to help her for no other reason than she needs help."
